    <section title="Introduction">
      <t>
      This document analyzes GTP-U specifications and 5GS architectural requirements and shows the 
      result.  GTP-U is a user plane protocol standardized in 3GPP and it is used widly in the 
      current mobile networks defined by 3GPP. 5GS is the next generation mobile network system 
      and it is under standardizing in 3GPP. 
      </t>

      <t>
      The resulds would be helpful for clarifying potencial issues on GTP-U in 5G system and it 
      would lead to improve and expand mobile user plane capability.
      </t>

      <t>
      In addition, it is proceeded to propose several IETF technologies 
      (<xref target="I-D.bogineni-dmm-optimized-mobile-user-plane"/>), and this document 
      provides criteria from the analysis for evaluating GTP-U and such protocols.
      </t>
    </section>
      
